race.description: Tabtouch Past The Post Payouts Maiden
race.comment: WYNN LAS VEGAS (5) flew home on debut before being left with too much to do once again at Bunbury at his second start, though he jumped an odds-on pop in both outings. He's likely to be well back again first-up here, but Pike sticks from the latest trial and he'll be hard to beat if he's come on in the break. BATISTA (6) stuck on well fresh, beaten 3L in a stronger race 18 days ago. The rise in trip looks a good move and he should get every chance from the inside draw. Chris Parnham takes the reins and he can put his best foot forward. QUEEN SELYSE (12) wasn't far away over this trip at Bunbury last time out and that form has worked out well. Remains down in the weights here for Nottle and she can be in the finish. FLYING MARADONA (10) has claims in a suitable race on debut. ACQUIRED TASTE (14) trialled better than the fresh run suggested and she can improve out in trip and with the blinkers on.
